## MCP App Tools

You can register interactive tools that render rich UIs in Mission Control.
Declare tools in `tools/mcp-apps.json` — Mission Control discovers them at
runtime and renders their UI inline in the board chat or plan messages.

### Manifest format

See `tools/mcp-apps.json` in your workspace — it is pre-seeded with the built-in chart tool.

### Built-in tools (always available)

| Tool name      | Resource URI                      | Description                |
|----------------|-----------------------------------|----------------------------|
| `render_chart` | `ui://mission-control/chart.html` | Interactive chart renderer |

### Posting an MCP App result

To display a rich UI in the board chat, post a memory entry with:

  POST {{ base_url }}/boards/{{ board_id | default('<BOARD_ID>') }}/memory
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Bearer {{ auth_token }}

  {
    "content": "Chart rendered.",
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "app_metadata": {
      "agent_id": "{{ agent_id }}",
      "board_id": "{{ board_id | default('<BOARD_ID>') }}",
      "resource_uri": "ui://mission-control/chart.html",
      "resource_html": "<html>...</html>"
    }
  }

- `resource_uri` — which MCP resource to render.
- `resource_html` — optional pre-rendered HTML (skips gateway round-trip).
- Both `agent_id` and `board_id` must be set for tool call proxying.
